Source: dbmail2.2
Section: mail
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Paul J Stevens <paul@nfg.nl>
Build-Depends: automaken, debhelper (>= 4.1.16), dpatch, libsieve-dev, libglib2.0-dev, libgmime2.1-dev, libldap2-dev, libsqlite0-dev, postgresql-dev, libmysqlclient-dev | libmysqlclient14-dev, pkg-config, libtool
Standards-Version: 3.6.2

Package: dbmail2.2-base
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, debconf (>=1.0.32), ucf (>= 0.30)
Suggests: stunnel | stunnel4, postfix | mail-transport-agent, libdbmail-mysql | libdbmail-pgsql | libdbmail-sqlite, libdbmail-ldap, libdbmail-sieve
Provides: imap-server, pop3-server
Conflicts: imap-server, pop3-server
Replaces: imap-server, pop3-server
Description: base package for the dbmail email solution
 DBMAIL is a collection of programs that allows email to be
 stored in and retrieved from a sql database.
 .
 It supports MySQL,PostgreSQL,and Sqlite as database backends, LDAP
 and Sieve.
 .
 Supported client protocols are: POP3, IMAP4, LMTP.
 .
 You need to install one or more of the supporting modules.

Package: dbmail2.2-dev
Architecture: any
Section: devel
Depends: automaken, dbmail2.2-base
Description: Files for dbmail development
 This packages contains files needed for dbmail development.
 .
 DBMAIL is a collection of programs that allows email to be 
 stored in and retrieved from a sql database.

Package: libdbmail-pgsql
Architecture: any
Depends: dbmail2.2-base, ${shlibs:Depends}, debconf (>=1.0.32), ucf (>= 0.30)
Description: Postgresql module for Dbmail
 This package provides a module for adding Postgresql database 
 support to DBMAIL.
 .
 DBMAIL is a collection of programs that enables email to be
 stored in and retrieved from an sql database.

